    "start_sources": "              {\r\n  \"files\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"name\": \"index.html\",\r\n      \"data\": \"<!DOCTYPE html>\\n<html>\\n  <head>\\n    <link rel=\\\"stylesheet\\\" href=\\\"style.css\\\">\\n  </head>\\n  <body>\\n    \\n    <!-- instruction paragraph -->\\n    <p>Give the first hyperlink a \\\"highlight\\\" class attribute. <br>Then, add the hover pseudo-class state to first link using its class attribute:</p> \\n    \\n    <!-- 1) Give the first hyperlink a \\\"highlight\\\" class attribute -->\\n    <!-- hyperlink to Google -->\\n    <a href=\\\"https://www.google.com/\\\">Google</a>\\n    <br>\\n    <br>\\n    <!-- hyperlink to Qwant -->\\n    <a href=\\\"https://www.qwant.com/?l=en\\\">Qwant</a>\\n\\n\\n\\n  </body>\\n</html>\"\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      \"name\": \"style.css\",\r\n      \"data\": \"/* 1) Add a rule for the \\\"hover\\\" state of the anchor tag using its \\\"highlight\\\" class attribute in the selector */\\n\\n/* 2) Style this state with a different background-color and large font size. */\\n\\n/* 3) Add any other different styles to each state of your choice. */\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n/* paragraph style */\\np {\\n  font-family: sans-serif;\\n  font-size: 24px;\\n  background-color: #ffa2e6;\\n}\"\r\n    }\r\n  ]\r\n}\r\n            ",
